String Functions:
1. Convert all patient names to uppercase.
2. Find the length of each staff member's name.
3. Concatenate staff_id and staff_name with a hyphen separator.

Sol:
1, USE Challenge;
SELECT upper(name) as Patient from patients;
2, USE Challenge;
SELECT name, length(name) as Len from patients;
3, USE Challenge;
SELECT concat_ws("-",staff_id,staff_name)  as IDNAME from staff;

Challenge :Create a patient summary that shows patient_id, full name in uppercase, service in lowercase, age category (if age >= 65 then 'Senior', if age >= 18 then 'Adult', else 'Minor'), and name length. 
Only show patients whose name length is greater than 10 characters.

Sol:
USE Challenge;
SELECT patient_id,upper(name) as name,lower(service) as service,
case
when age>=65 then 'Senior'
when age>=18 then 'Adult'
else 'Minor'
end
as age_category
from patients;
